## Rules

- `description`: ≤1000 chars; factual; no marketing fluff. Lead with what the protocol DOES, not adjectives.
- `providerLogoUrl`: always `null`. The logo-assets normalizer fills it from RootData `provider_logo_url`/`anchors.providerLogoUrl`, downloads it under `out/protocol-logo/`, and rewrites it to the OneKey static-logo CDN path.
- `tags`: 3-8 lowercase tokens, no spaces, e.g. `yield`, `fixed-rate`, `eth-l2`, `lst`.
- `establishment`: integer year. Treat RootData's `anchors.establishment.value` as strong evidence; use fetched primary sources when they contradict it.
- `providerWebsite`: official site URL. Treat `validated_overrides.providerWebsite` as strong evidence, but prefer a better-supported fetched official URL if it conflicts.
- `providerXLink`: official X account URL. Treat `validated_overrides.providerXLink` as strong evidence, but verify against the official website/docs when possible.
- `providerDiscordLink`: invite URL or null.
- `status`: always `"draft"`.
- `type`: pick exactly one of `fixed_rate`, `simple_earn`, `staking` based on evidence:
  - `fixed_rate`: protocols offering fixed/predictable yields, principal/yield separation, or PT/YT-style products (e.g., Pendle, Term Finance, Notional).
  - `simple_earn`: deposit-and-earn yield products — vaults, savings rates, money markets, yield-bearing stablecoins (e.g., Yearn vaults, sUSDe-style yield-bearing stablecoins, lending money markets where deposit yield is the primary product).
  - `staking`: native staking, liquid staking, or restaking products (e.g., Lido, Rocket Pool, EigenLayer).
  - If `{{HINTS}}` contains category language such as fixed-rate, PT/YT, simple earn, vault, staking, LST, or LRT, use it only as a research clue. Do not treat it as an authoritative type value. Record your rationale in `handoff_notes[]` when the classification is non-obvious, e.g., `{ "target": "metadata", "note": "evidence indicates simple_earn because USDat is a yield-bearing stablecoin", "source": "https://..." }`.

